The paper deals with relativizations of complexity classes and their theories, which are topics typically studied in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of Wilson's stack oracle model suggests a connection to logic and automata theory (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the collapse of complexity classes, which is a topic in computational complexity theory and circuit complexity (cs.CS). The development of theories that characterize relativized subclasses of \Ptime\ suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
